description:
Implement the full server-side heal action, covering both self-targeting and other-targeting through a single :heal action.

Infrastructure to add in UndercityServer.Player.Server:
1. handle_call({:take_heal, amount}, ...) — symmetric to take_damage; guards at HP == 0 ({:error, :collapsed}); returns {:error, :already_full} if already at max HP; otherwise applies heal and saves.
2. handle_call({:self_heal, item_name, ap_cost}, ...) — atomic single-callback for self-targeting. Checks not collapsed, applies AP regen, validates item is a Remedy, checks HP not already full, spends AP, removes item, applies heal, saves. Returns {:ok, item, heal_amount, new_ap, new_hp} or an appropriate error.

Add Player.take_heal/2 public function (analogous to Player.take_damage/2).

New Actions.Heal module:
- Accepts (player_id, block_id, target_id, item_name)
- Branches on player_id == target_id:
  - Self: calls Player.self_heal/3 (single GenServer call — avoids deadlock)
  - Other: pre-checks target HP via Player.constitution before spending; calls Player.use_item/3 on actor, then Player.take_heal/2 on target
- Pre-checks (other-heal): target in block, target not collapsed, target not at full HP, actor has Salve
- Looks up heal amount via Remedy.effect/1 before any GenServer calls
- Includes a notification stub (notifies target on success via the channel from undercity-w6m)

New Gateway.perform clause:
  def perform(player_id, block_id, :heal, {target_id, item_name})

Response shapes:
  {:ok, {:healed, target_id, new_ap, new_hp}}
  {:error, :invalid_target}
  {:error, :not_a_remedy}
  {:error, :already_full}
  {:error, :collapsed}
  {:error, :exhausted}
  {:error, :item_missing}
